  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can I tell if a guy likes me or is just using me?",
  "response": "Determining whether a guy likes you or is just using you can be challenging, but there are some signs you can look for to help you assess the situation. Here are a few indicators to consider:\n\n1. **Consistency in Communication**: If he frequently reaches out to you and maintains dialogue, it\u2019s a good sign he values your interaction. If he only contacts you when it\u2019s convenient for him, he may not be genuinely interested.\n\n2. **Effort in the Relationship**: Pay attention to how much effort he puts into spending time with you, making plans, and getting to know you. A genuine interest often involves him initiating dates and finding ways to connect.\n\n3. **Investment in Your Life**: A guy who likes you will show interest in your thoughts, feelings, and experiences. He will ask questions about your life and be supportive of your goals and interests.\n\n4. **Physical Affection**: If he expresses consistent physical affection (holding hands, hugging, etc.) and seeks opportunities to be close to you, it can indicate genuine feelings. If the affection feels limited to physical or sexual interactions without deeper connection, he might not be serious.\n\n5. **Future Plans**: Someone who is truly interested will discuss future plans that include you, whether it's future dates, vacations, or other long-term ideas. If he avoids talking about the future or his intentions, it may be a red flag.\n\n6. **Respect for Boundaries**: A guy who genuinely likes you will respect your boundaries and will be willing to communicate openly about your relationship. If he often pushes boundaries or ignores your comfort levels, he may not have your best interests in mind.\n\n7. **Mixed Signals**: If his behavior is inconsistent\u2014sometimes charming and affectionate, other times distant or unavailable\u2014it could indicate that he is not fully committed or is unsure about his feelings.\n\n8. **How He Treats Others**: Observe how he treats friends, family, and even strangers. A kind and respectful demeanor towards others can reflect his character and how he might treat you in the long run.\n\nUltimately, clear and open communication is key. If you're feeling uncertain about his intentions, consider discussing your feelings with him directly to gain clarity on where you both stand. Trust your instincts and prioritize your emotional well-being in any relationship.",
